  {project_id: 360, component_name: "Design Services", description: "", expected_outcome: "", remarks: "*Pre-design services already submitted and approved by the Chancellor.\r\n*Pending approval of the submitted indicative master planning services which includes preliminary cost estimate. Consultant was advised to do value engineering.\r\n*The consultant submitted revised indicative master planning services on July 22, 2015. Pending approval by the TWG and the Chancellor.\r\n*Comments and suggestions for the revised indicative master planning services were forwarded to A.C. Ong last July 31, 2015. Pending submission of the revised design from A.C. Ong.\r\n*As of August 19, 2015, no movement on the design phase. UPOU's Assistant to the Vice Chancellor for Finance and Administration, Prof. Luna will follow-up A.C. Ong regarding their next submission.", percent_accomplishment: "15.0", percent_accomplishment_by: "2015-06-16 00:00:00", bidding_contractor: "A.C. Ong Consulting Services", bidding_number: 1, bidding_award: "2015-03-27 00:00:00", bidding_proceed: "2015-04-24 00:00:00", financial_budget: "1050000.0", financial_contract_price: nil, financial_actual_cost: nil, financial_source: "", timeline_target_start: nil, timeline_target_end: nil, timeline_actual_start: "2015-04-24 00:00:00", timeline_actual_end: nil, bidding_remarks: "", financial_remarks: "", timeline_remarks: "", end_user: "The three faculties of study of UPOU - FMDS, FICS, FEd.", timeline_duration: 7, timeline_extension: nil, financial_variation: nil, status: nil, completed_by: nil, classification: nil},
  {project_id: 358, component_name: "Provision of Solar Power System in UPOU Community Hub Building", description: "The provision of a Solar Photovoltaic (PV) system in the UPOU Community Hub building is in line with the UP Systemâs goal of promoting the use of green technology through all its constituent universities. The solar PV system shall be a grid-tied system to be connected to the MERALCOâs grid. Several electrical loads in the building shall be using the electricity harnessed by the system while the excess electricity generated by the system shall be supplied to the grid and the equivalent amount of this electricity shall be deducted to the electric bill of the UPOU. The usage of this green technology is intended to help UPOU in its drive for increased energy efficiency.", expected_outcome: "", remarks: "*Financial proposal of the bidder with the highest rating in technical proposal opened on 26 May 2015.\r\n*Materials to be used for approval as of June 30, 2015.\r\n*Pre-construction meeting held July 10, 2015. It was agreed that the contract time would be temporarily suspended until the full turn-over of the Community Hub on July 21, 2015.\r\n*RC De Villa submitted request for time suspension dated July 14, 2015\r\n*Contract time resumed on July 27, 2015\r\n*RC De Villa submitted a letter stating that they are just waiting for the delivery of the materials after which installation shall follow.", percent_accomplishment: nil, percent_accomplishment_by: nil, bidding_contractor: "RC De Villa Construction & Development Corporation", bidding_number: 1, bidding_award: "2015-06-05 00:00:00", bidding_proceed: "2015-07-08 00:00:00", financial_budget: "2910675.72", financial_contract_price: "2356221.55", financial_actual_cost: nil, financial_source: "", timeline_target_start: nil, timeline_target_end: "2015-09-30 00:00:00", timeline_actual_start: nil, timeline_actual_end: nil, bidding_remarks: "", financial_remarks: "", timeline_remarks: "", end_user: "", timeli